ary-keeping, science, travel, and a love of books-and their divergent enthusiasms, Pepys for theater and music, Evelyn for horticulture and garden design. Through the richly documented lives of two remarkable men, Willes revisits the history of London and of England in an age of regicide, revolution, fire, and plague to reveal it also as a time of enthralling possibility.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Jun 2019) 7aHISTORY / Modern / 17th Century.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300231724423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300231724.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles